HOW TO INSTALL SIMBRAILLESimBraille is a Macintosh font that will allow you to read simulated braille in applications such as word processing and web browsers (Netscape, Internet Explorer, etc.).To install SimBraille:1.  Quit all of your applications (not really necessary, but helpful).2.  Double-click to open your hard drive.3.  Double-click on the folder titled "System Folder"4. Find the folder entitled "Fonts".  Drag the SimBraille icon into your Fonts folder.5.  Restart your Macintosh.You should now be able to see simulated braille in your applications.